import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    box_plot_data = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].apply(list)
    plt.boxplot(box_plot_data, labels=box_plot_data.index.year)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across budget years?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['forecastYear'], data['value'])
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.title('What is the trend of values over forecast years?', wrap=True)

        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['value'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across forecast years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;
